<p>
    The following problems all involve a sign
    hung from two different ropes.
    There are three forces acting on each sign.
</p>

<ul class="principleList">
    <li>
        <strong>Gravity:</strong>
        <ul>
            <li>
                The direction is always down,
                or the -Y direction.
            </li>
            <li>
                The magnitude is given by \( F_g = mg \)
            </li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>The Two Tension Forces</strong>:
        These are two forces applied by each of the two ropes.
        <ul>
            <li>
                The direction is typically between the two
                axes and must be broken into components.
            </li>
            <li>
                The magnitude is not a set value,
                and it can be known or unknown.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ul>

<p>
    These are <strong>statics problems</strong>,
    the sign is not moving.
    This means
    $$
    \Sigma F_x = 0 \; \; \; \; \; \; \; \; \Sigma F_y = 0
    $$
    These facts can be used to determine any unknown information.
</p>

